4:
PARADISE ISLE!
A place of BEAUTY—and equally
great VICE. A veritable garden,
where desire reigns supreme!
8:
Far from falling to temptation, let us
be like the BEAUTIFUL flowers that
abound—blooming and blossoming,
with pride!
12:
Let us be beacons of TRUE ELEGANCE
in this paradise we've found!
20:
Very... dramatic of you, Marguerite.
Say, aren't you from the Endless Blue
yourself? Will you be stopping by to
see your family?
24:
Ah, your concern—though PURE and
HUMBLE—is entirely unnecessary. I've
long since severed ties with them!
26:
Regardless! I've been to Paradise
Isle many a time before, so you can
trust me to be your guide!
30:
I will show you the BEAUTY this island
holds!
37:
I was just wondering why things got
so quiet—Marguerite's not here.
41:
She said she had to go get changed
and went off to some boutique she'd
been to before.
44: A new outfit, huh? This I gotta see.
48:
It will no doubt be something quite
beautiful, though knowing her it will
also probably be... bold.
52:
Look over there! Wow, she looks so
cool!
53: Oh my gosh, she's coming this way!
58:
Ladies and gentlemen—I'm terribly
sorry to make you wait!
67:
Why, my dear, who else could I
possibly be?
75:
I can't believe I'm sayin' this, but I
agree. You look like a flower or
somethin'.
78:
Bro, look over there, man. We gotta
go say something! Look at that girl,
bro, she's like, a total snack.
81:
Yo, I don't need you to tell me that,
bro. I know a hot girl when I see one!
'Ight just watch me go, I got this.
83:
H-hey, babe. How YOU doing? You,
uh, wanna go grab a drink with us or
something?
(...Nailed it!)
85:
Just so you know, our bro is SUPER
loaded. If you stick with us we can
party hard all night! Tell her, bro!
87:
I mean it's not MY money so much
as it is my parents' money, but
whatever. Yo, did I mention I have
THREE boats?
89:
So whaddya think? Wanna come
party with us? Me and my bros are
also super jacked, if we see any
nerds creepin' on you, we'll protect
you!
96:
Why are you quaking like that? What
happened to all your grandstanding?
99:
That tough-guy act, that crude,
thoughtless demeanor! Your
pompous peacock-like strut! I see
through it.
103:
Throw it all away! End the charade
and lay yourselves BARE.
114:
I almost feel bad for those kids.
Almost.
117:
Wh-wha? Wait a minute, like, what
are you saying, exactly?
122:
Say what you wanted to say one
more time. But this time, look me in
the eyes and speak the truth. Set it
free from the cage of your heart!
124:
One more time, without the bravado
and blatant lies. Once more, without
showing off. Tell me, who are you?!
134:
I'm Scott!
I'm the leader... or at least I always
try to be, but really I'm pretty
insecure.
136:
I'm John!
I'm pretty good with my hands—I
really want to be a craftsman one
day...
138:
I'm Gary!
I really love clothes and have a
dream of being a fashion designer...
140:
We... saw you and thought you were
beautiful, which is why we
approached you. We really respect
you, as a person!
142:
Yeah, exactly, we're all about the
RESPECT! We'll treat you well and
take you wherever you want!
145:
Would you please...
Go on a date with the three of us?
153:
Wonderful! Well then, let's go! Take
me wherever you please, then I will
do the same in return. But wherever
we go, let it be somewhere
MARVELOUS!
156:
She said yes? This has never happ—I
mean, yeah, let's go!
159:
My name is Marguerite, pursuer of
all things GORGEOUS.
162:
Let's be off, then! Onward, to even
greater beauty!
168:
The whole 'beauty' thing is great and
all, but don't forget we've got plans
later, eh?
172:
Hehe. Of course I haven't forgotten!
But the pursuit of beauty takes
precedence—even should my body
give out, I will press on!
176:
So... you're gonna party till you
collapse?
179:
Whoa, you guys have a beastfolk
friend? That's so cool... I wish I had a
beastfolk friend...
181:
Hey, why don't you ALL come along?
The more bros the merrier, bros!
183:
Heck yeah, that's what I'm talking
about! Let's all go together!
All right, squad, roll out!
